Prime Minister has written to First Great Western to 'urgently review' plans to increase fares on route between London and the Cotswolds . 
  David Cameron has promised to freeze fares in real terms for the whole of the next parliament . 
  Passengers travelling with rail firm could face increases of up to 87 per cent from May 17 . 
  First GreatWestern plans to almost double some fares on the route through his Witney constituency . 
  Virgin has also announced a series of price hikes on routes through his constituency . 
 